workflow.description:
# Generate Videos from Images with Wan 2.2 I2V A14B AI Model

### üåç Overview

This workflow connects **n8n** with **Replicate‚Äôs Wan-Video model** to generate **video content from an image + prompt**.
It handles:

* üîë API authentication
* üì§ Sending a generation request
* ‚è≥ Polling until completion
* üì• Returning a downloadable video link

---

## üü¢ Section 1: Start & Authentication

üîó **Nodes:**
1Ô∏è‚É£ **On clicking 'execute' (Manual Trigger)**
‚ñ∂Ô∏è Starts the workflow manually when you click *Execute Workflow*.

2Ô∏è‚É£ **Set API Key**
üîë Stores your **Replicate API Key** securely inside n8n.

* Value: `YOUR_REPLICATE_API_KEY`

üí° **Beginner Benefit**:
‚úÖ No need to hardcode API keys in every request
‚úÖ Easy to swap keys for different accounts

---

## üîµ Section 2: Send Video Generation Request

üîó **Nodes:**
3Ô∏è‚É£ **Create Prediction (HTTP Request)**
üì§ Sends a request to Replicate API ‚Üí `/v1/predictions`

* Model: `wan-video/wan-2.2-i2v-a14b`
* Input Parameters:

  * üìù `prompt` ‚Üí your text description
  * üñºÔ∏è `image` ‚Üí input video/image URL
  * üé≤ `seed` ‚Üí reproducibility
  * üéûÔ∏è `num_frames` ‚Üí 81 frames
  * ‚è© `sample_shift` ‚Üí 5
  * ‚öôÔ∏è `sample_steps` ‚Üí 30
  * üé¨ `frames_per_second` ‚Üí 16

4Ô∏è‚É£ **Extract Prediction ID (Code)**
üÜî Pulls out the **prediction ID + status** from Replicate‚Äôs response.
This ID is needed for polling until the video finishes generating.

üí° **Beginner Benefit**:
‚úÖ Automates the API call to generate video
‚úÖ Extracts ID ‚Üí avoids manual copy-paste

---

## üü£ Section 3: Polling & Status Check

üîó **Nodes:**
5Ô∏è‚É£ **Wait (2 sec)**
‚è≥ Adds a short delay before checking progress.

* Prevents API spam

6Ô∏è‚É£ **Check Prediction Status (HTTP Request)**
üîÑ Calls Replicate API ‚Üí `/v1/predictions/{id}`

* Checks whether the video is still processing or finished

7Ô∏è‚É£ **Check If Complete (IF Node)**
‚ùì Compares status ‚Üí `succeeded` or not

* ‚úÖ If complete ‚Üí goes to **Process Result**
* ‚ùå If not ‚Üí loops back to **Wait** and tries again

üí° **Beginner Benefit**:
‚úÖ Automatic re-checking ‚Üí you don‚Äôt need to refresh manually
‚úÖ Works until result is ready

---

## üü° Section 4: Process Final Result

üîó **Nodes:**
8Ô∏è‚É£ **Process Result (Code)**
üì• Once complete, extracts:

* ‚úÖ Status
* üéûÔ∏è Output video URL
* üìä Generation metrics
* ‚è±Ô∏è Timestamps (created\_at, completed\_at)
* üß© Model used

Final output = direct **video URL** you can download/share üé•

---

## üìä Final Overview

| Section   | What Happens                   | Why It‚Äôs Useful                   |
| --------- | ------------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| üü¢ Auth   | Manual Trigger + API Key       | Secure, easy start                |
| üîµ Send   | Create Prediction + Extract ID | Kicks off video generation        |
| üü£ Poll   | Wait + Check Status + IF       | Auto-checks progress until done   |
| üü° Result | Process Result                 | Gives final video link + metadata |

---

## üöÄ Why This Workflow Rocks

* üé• **Video from Image + Prompt** ‚Üí AI-powered video generation in minutes
* üîÑ **Fully automated** ‚Üí from request to final video, no manual checks
* üîë **Secure** ‚Üí API keys handled safely
* ‚öôÔ∏è **Customizable** ‚Üí tweak frames, FPS, prompt, seed

---

‚ú® With this workflow, you‚Äôve got a **personal AI video generator** inside n8n ‚Äî all you need to do is provide a prompt + input image/video, and you‚Äôll get a fresh AI video link back.

---

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
